                <Header>Reports</Header>
                <Paragraph>The monthly report "CDC Vital Signs" is released on the first Tuesday of every month. Past editions addressed such topics as colorectal and breast cancer screening; obesity, alcohol and tobacco use; HIV testing; motor vehicle safety; cardiovascular disease; teen pregnancy and infections associated with health care; and foodborne diseases. The report is also available in Spanish.</Paragraph>
            </EntitySourceOfInformation>
